  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.2.0 (02cb1c0 2022-12-26T10:50:48.513690086Z)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nscript\n\n### Operating System\n\nLinux\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen running a script on polygon mumbai, I get a massive tx fee when deploying and the error below.\r\n`(code: -32000, message: tx fee (23897849040572194725236092048628893714261946156005195776.00 ether) exceeds the configured cap (100.00 ether), data: None)`\r\n\r\nI have been able to deploy on goerli without an issue and have also tried using different rpc endpoints/deploying another contract but the same error persists.",
